"v.断言，主张 【英】 v. 断言，主张(to state positively; declare, affirm) 【考】 calumny : assertion / perjury : testimony(诽谤是假断言/伪证 是假证词)反义词：diffidence( 羞怯，缺乏自信) 【记】 as+sert(参与)→一再 参与(讨论)→主张 【同】 派生词: assertive(adj. 言语果断的，断言的) ; assertiveness(n. 坚定而自信); assertion(n.坚决断 言) 【例】 The lawyer asserted that his client was innocent. v. 断言(肯定地说出); 坚持己见(大胆地或强有力地提出观点, 使其为大家所知) = aver = avouch = avow = constate = depose = profess 【例】I had to assert myself in the meeting 我在会上不得不坚持自己的观点. assert sth to be true 断言某事是真实的 【记】as一再, sert参与－一再参与(讨论)－断言, 主张 【类】calumny: assertion = perjury: testimony诽谤是假断言 = 伪证是假证词assert: belabor = tend: fuss过分断言是冗长分析 = 过分照顾是大惊小怪 【记】insert 插了一句话断言，宣称；很certain的说出 【相关】assert 断言，声称，desert 沙漠，放弃，逃跑，dessert 甜点，dissert 论述，exsert(向外+突起)突出，insert(向内突起)插入 assert (v.)  c.1600, ""declare,"" from Latin assertus, past participle of asserere ""claim, maintain, affirm"" (see assertion). Related: Asserted; asserting. To assert oneself ""stand up for one's rights"" is recorded from 1879."
